jobs.prompt:
Warm the Aria purchasing intelligence cache before the workday. Run getPurchasingIntelligence and persist the snapshot so the dashboard is instantly ready when Will arrives.

Steps:
1. cd /c/Users/BuildASoil/Documents/Projects/aria
2. Run: node --import tsx -e "
import { FinaleClient } from './src/lib/finale/client.ts';
import { writeFileSync, mkdirSync } from 'fs';
import { join } from 'path';
const cacheDir = join(process.cwd(), '.aria-cache', 'purchasing');
mkdirSync(cacheDir, { recursive: true });
console.log('[warm] Starting scan...');
const client = new FinaleClient();
const groups = await client.getPurchasingIntelligence(365);
const totalItems = groups.reduce((s,g) => s + g.items.length, 0);
console.log('[warm] Complete: ' + groups.length + ' groups, ' + totalItems + ' items');
writeFileSync(join(cacheDir, 'purchasing-resale.json'), JSON.stringify({ at: Date.now(), value: groups }));
console.log('[warm] Cache saved.');
"
3. Report: how many items and groups were cached, and whether the dashboard now shows fresh data (check http://localhost:3001/api/dashboard/purchasing?mode=all).

Note: this takes 12-15 min due to Finale API rate limiting. The timeout in cache.ts is already 15 min. If it times out, report the error and the cron should retry on next weekday.
